news.title: Oberoi Realty's profit rises 20% to Rs 319 crore in Q2 FY23
news.para: Total income, however, declined to Rs 711.79 crore in the second quarter of this fiscal year from Rs 768.52 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year.

news.title: Over 85,000 apply for 477 YEIDA residential plots
news.para: Under this scheme, the 477 plots of nine different sizes ranging from 60 sqm to 2,000 sqm are available. These plots will be allotted in five sectors of the Yamuna Expressway region through a draw of lots.

news.title: Not evaluating proposal to buy Jaypee Group's cement business: Adani
news.para: Adani had told Ambuja Cements and ACC employees that he plans to double the cement making capacity to 140 million tons from existing 70 million tons by 2027.

news.title: Supertech twin tower: SC directs refund to 15 buyers from Rs 1 crore deposited by IRP
news.para: The top court was hearing a batch of contempt petitions filed by home buyers seeking a refund as per the last year's order of court.

news.title: Rs 60,000 crore target set, YEIDA plans more land schemes
news.para: To meet this target, officials said, the Yamuna Expressway Industrial Development Authority (YEIDA) is planning to launch several commercial and group housing schemes before Diwali this year.

news.title: Government relaxes TOD policy, slashes FSI rates to boost realty along Pune Metro
news.para: The FSI rate has been reduced from 60% to 30% for residential properties of the ready reckoner (RR) rates following the government's approval to the relaxed TOD policy on roads that have a width of nine metre and more.

news.title: No draws for Vadodara civic body's housing project yet
news.para: In August last year, the VMC was stunned when a row over manipulation of lists of beneficiaries had raised head. The allegations were found to be correct and it emerged that two officials had changed the lists.

news.title: Indiabulls Commercial Credit acquires south Delhi property for Rs 60 crore
news.para: South Delhi and the Lutyens Bungalow Zone, New Delhi’s answer to London’s Greenwich or Mayfair, have registered the highest number of property registrations in three years, with uber-rich investors buying assets in areas where demand usually outruns supply.

news.title: Bollywood producer Renu Chopra buys apartment in Mumbai for Rs 48 crore
news.para: The deal values the apartment on a carpet-area basis at Rs 1.51 lakh per sq ft, pushing it in the tally of the country’s most expensive transactions for a residential apartment. The deal can be counted as an outlier as the rate is higher than the ongoing range of Rs 85,000 to Rs 1 lakh per sq ft in the vicinity.

news.title: Vishal Bhardwaj's family buys apartment in Mumbai for Rs 19.5 crore
news.para: The Bhardwaj family has purchased the apartment spread over a built up area of 2,056 sq ft on the 21st floor of residential tower Bay View and have paid stamp duty of Rs 1.17 crore for the registration of the deal.

news.title: Over 100 complaints daily, Dehradun civic body says 'only 500 defunct streetlights'
news.para: The DMC claims of the 97,949 streetlights in 100 wards of Dehradun, less than 500 are currently defunct. Bhupender Kathait, councilor, Hathibarkala, said this couldn't be true, as "in every ward, at least 10 to 12 lights are defunct".

news.title: Shree Cement's net profit dips 67% in Q2 FY23
news.para: The company's total consolidated income stood at Rs 4,197.37 crore in Q2 FY23, a growth of 19 per cent from Rs 3,526.95 crore it recorded in the similary quarter last year.

news.title: Pune: 88,000 citizens use chatbot for property tax services
news.para: After introducing the service for property tax, the PMC is now making it available for water tax payment too. This chatbot will also provide services such as death and birth certificates.

news.title: Nashik civic body to link building completion certificate to property tax
news.para: ​​The panel members include the deputy director (town planning), assistant director of town planning, deputy commissioner (garden) and town planner of the civic body.

news.title: Pune: Houses soon for PMAY beneficiaries in Wadgaon Khurd
news.para: The review of project works was carried out by a delegation of the Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) officials on Thursday.
